[2] Europe: ECDC update
Date: Fri 18 May 2018
Source: DG Alerts from European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) [edited]
http://dgalerts.docguide.com/europe-update-measles-7600-cases-inc-22-deaths-4-countries


Europe -- update: measles, over 7600 cases including 22 deaths in 4 countries
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Measles outbreaks continue to occur in a number of EU/EEA countries, with a risk of spread and sustained transmission in areas with susceptible populations. The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) provided the latest situation update in its weekly Communicable Disease Threats Report (CDTR) published on 18 May 2018 [http://https://ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications-data/monthly-measles-and-rubella-monitoring-report-may-2018].

Since the previous monthly report published on [13 Apr 2018], updates are provided for 17 EU/EFTA countries. In 2018 and as of 17 May, most of the cases in the EU are reported from Romania (2712), France (2173), Greece (1948), and Italy (805). 22 deaths have been reported in 2018 from Romania (15), Italy (4), Greece (2), and France (1).

The Czech Republic has reported 103 cases of measles across the country in 2018, as of 30 Mar 2018. This is an increase of 74 cases since the previous CDTR on 13 Apr 2018. Among the reported cases, the majority were reported from Prague (70), over half of the cases were not vaccinated and 19 per cent were children 1-4 years of age.

France has reported 2173 cases between 1 Jan and 13 May 2018. This is an increase of 568 cases since 8 Apr 2018. Since the beginning of the outbreak in November 2017 there have been 2231 cases, including 1 death, reported across the country. Of all cases, 48 per cent are from New Aquitaine region. The highest incidence is in children under 1 year of age. Among the reported cases, 22 per cent were hospitalised and 87 per cent were not or incompletely vaccinated.

Greece has reported 1948 cases in 2018 as of 17 May, including 2 deaths. This is an increase of 416 cases and one death since the CDTR published on 13 Apr 2018. As of 17 May 2018, and since the beginning of the outbreak in May 2017, Greece has reported 2916 measles cases, of which 1712 were laboratory confirmed. Among the laboratory-confirmed cases, 4 deaths were reported. Most of the cases occurred in southern Greece among young Roma children and young Greek adults. However, an increase in measles cases in northern Greece has been notified.

Italy has reported 805 cases of measles, including 4 deaths, between 1 Jan and 31 Mar 2018. This is an increase of 394 cases and 2 deaths since the CDTR was last published on 13 Apr 2018. Among the cases there were 38 healthcare professionals. Of all cases reported by the 18 regions, over 87 per cent were from 5 regions: Sicily, Lazio, Campania, Calabria, and Lombardy. Among the cases, 92 per cent were unvaccinated and 2 per cent received 1 dose.

Romania reported 2712 measles cases, including 15 deaths, in 2018, as of 11 May. This is an increase of 1003 cases and 6 deaths since previous CDTR on 13 Apr 2018. Since the beginning of the outbreak in October 2016 and as of 6 Apr 2018, Romania has reported 12 991 confirmed measles cases, including 52 deaths.

UK: between 1 Jan and 9 May 2018, 440 confirmed measles cases were reported in England, with London (164), the South East (86), West Midlands (78), South West (42), and West Yorkshire (37) reporting the most cases. The majority of cases (54 per cent) are over 15 years of age. The commonest strain is the B3 genotype currently circulating in Romania.

Austria has reported 43 measles cases in 2018, as of 4 May, an increase of 14 cases since 13 Apr 2018.

Bulgaria has reported 4 cases of measles in 2018, as of 13 May, an increase by 1 case since 13 Apr 2018.

Finland has reported 3 cases of measles in 2018, as of 17 May, an increase of 2 cases since 26 Feb 2018; the recent 2 cases were imported.

Germany has reported 176 cases of measles in 2018, as of 21 Apr. This is an increase of 99 cases since the previous report.

Hungary reported 16 cases of measles in 2018, as of 6 May, an increase of 2 cases since 13 Apr 2018.

Ireland has reported 72 cases of measles in 2018, as of 12 May 2018, an increase of 12 cases since 13 Apr 2018.

Poland has reported 44 cases of measles in 2018, as of 30 Apr. This is an increase of 13 cases since 13 Apr 2018.

Portugal has reported 111 confirmed cases of measles in 2018, as of 8 Apr. This is an increase of 6 cases since 13 Apr 2018. In addition 24 cases are pending test results. Of the confirmed cases, 110 are adults and 88 (79 per cent) are healthcare professionals. Most of the cases (106) have been reported in the north of the country.

Spain has reported 105 cases in 2018, as of 6 May. Among these, 64 cases were reported from Valencia region and 20 cases from Catalonia.

Sweden has reported contact tracing in 2 hospitals of Stockholm county, after each had been visited by a measles case (in the last week of April and on 1 May 2018). No additional measles cases were reported.

Switzerland has reported 20 cases in 2018, as of 8 May. This is an increase of 6 cases since 13 Apr 2018.

