[3] Afghanistan: WHO
Date: Mon 30 Apr 2018
Source: WHO/EMRO [edited]
http://www.emro.who.int/images/stories/afghanistan/EHA_update_April_2018_FINAL_002.pdf


WHO -- Afghanistan situation report - April 2018
------------------------------------------------
Cases of measles continue to rise with more than 150 reported outbreaks and more than 2000 cases reported in the 1st 4 months of 2018. In addition to measles, major disease outbreaks included Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever (8) and pertussis (4).

Routine immunization was banned in several health centres at Watapur district in Kunar province.

