[5] Australia (Brisbane, Queensland): alert, travel related
Date: Mon 28 May 2018 4:07 PM AEST
Source: Brisbane Times [edited]
https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/measles-alert-for-brisbane-s-south-and-logan-20180528-p4zhzq.html


A case of measles has been confirmed in Brisbane's south, Queensland Health says. A child later diagnosed with measles travelled from Delhi to Brisbane, via Bangkok, on Tue 22 May 2018. [See source URL above for locations and flights where individuals may have been exposed.]

Metro South Health [MSH] staff have been contacting people who were in close contact with the child. MSH public health physician Bhakti Vasant said it was likely more cases of measles would appear in the following weeks due to the high number of people exposed. "If people are adequately vaccinated with 2 recorded doses of measles, mumps, rubella (MMR) vaccine, they are very unlikely to get the disease. People who are unsure or have concerns about their immunity to measles should contact their doctor to check whether they have had both vaccines," Dr Vasant said.

For information: https://metrosouth.health.qld.gov.au/news/measles-alert-for-brisbane.

[byline: Lucy Stone]

